<h2 style="font-size: 22px;">Southern Illinois University Carbondale</h2>
<strong>Carbondale, IL</strong>

<div class="infolines">
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers credit for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers placement into higher-level courses for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
</div>


<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>To receive AP credit, students must earn at least a grade of 3 and in some cases a 4 or 5. The maximum credit granted through advanced placement examinations is thirty hours (fifteen for an associate degree). It is nonresident credit, does not carry a grade, and is not used in computing the students' grade point average.  The credit to be granted is determined by the appropriate department. The credit will be validated after 12 hours credit of C average or better in residence at SIUC.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://transfer.siu.edu/nontraditional/index.html" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

 <p class="box-padding-3">
    Additional restrictions and requirements may apply to the policy listed below. For more detailed information, visit the college's AP policy on the Web or contact the college directly.
 </p>

